# C5 ordering — empirical evidence (cyril-84ca Slice 7)
# Probe: .cyril-84ca/notif_order.rs drives cyril's REAL bridge (spawn_bridge) against
# real kiro-cli 2.8.0 and reports the order AgentMessage vs TurnCompleted arrive on
# cyril's notification channel. Date: 2026-06-17.
#
# Question: does streamed agent text arrive before TurnCompleted on the notification
# channel, and does it differ by backend (v2 vs KAS)?

== v2 (kiro-cli acp, default engine) ==
agent_args = ["acp"]
order = ["msg", "msg", "TURN"]
AgentMessages: 2 before TURN, 0 after TURN (total 2)
=> OK: all 2 AgentMessages preceded TurnCompleted

== KAS / v3 (kiro-cli acp --agent-engine kas) ==
agent_args = ["acp", "--agent-engine", "kas"]
order = ["msg", "TURN"]
AgentMessages: 1 before TURN, 0 after TURN (total 1)
=> OK: all 1 AgentMessages preceded TurnCompleted

## Conclusion
Ordering HOLDS for BOTH v2 and KAS — not a v2/KAS difference. The reorder seen in the
zero-gap unit harness is a theoretical agent-client-protocol library race (responses
resolve inline; notifications are queued via incoming_tx), filed as cyril-9akh. Real
backends leave enough timing gap for the notification queue to drain before the
response resolves, so cyril never reorders in practice. cyril-84ca's off-loop change
neither causes nor regresses this (the pre-fix inline conn.prompt().await shared the
identical library behavior).

Bonus: KAS runs through cyril's current bridge today and maps its turn-end to
TurnCompleted (a real prompt response crosses the wire), not only session_info_update.
